reviews.text: Lots of cool stuff here eataries and some little cool surprise vending machines thatll give you random little stuff. You got your ikea and other types of stores here as well
Good place for dining

Considering the deterioration of our civilisation, fewer and fewer developments (especially in Hong Kong) actually made improvements to our life. But renovating the Cdw Building was an encouraging example that proved the value of human intelligence.

First, the new look of this building was refreshing, also, they introduced some big names, e.g. Ikea, and Physical fitness. The tea house there was also very popular, together with a good number of new eateries that brought new customers and keeping the strong one - Saizeriya Italian for attracting the original patrons. Quite a smart move!
